(9, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/cd64ab1cf6d07df0253d71e34ea4f475.webp', 'Honda Malaysia recalls 23,476 cars for Takata airbag inflator replacements', 13, 'BERNAMA', '2019-10-04', 'uploads/4f3b8d3d992ce9ddacbca483c50bfe65.webp', 'uploads/894f99fb4ddd56ee312aad9f53513167.jpeg', 'uploads/e6f72223e45b99b7af988552c591a22e.jpg', 'null', 'Honda Malaysia is recalling 23,476 Honda vehicles that were recalled earlier to replace the Takata front airbag inflators.\n\nIt said vehicle owners who are affected will receive notification letters from Honda Malaysia along with the details of the recall and stock availability.\n\n', '<p>The affected models recalled for the Takata front driver airbag inflator replacements are the Civic (model year 2006-2007 and 2009-2011), CR-V (2007-2008 and 2010-2011), Stream (2010 and 2012), Insight (2011-2012),  City (2009-2013) and Jazz (2012-2013).\n\nMeanwhile, the models recalled for Takata front passenger airbag inflator replacements are the Accord (model year 2003, 2005-2006, 2008-2009 and 2011-2012), Stream (2003-2005), CR-V (2002-2009), Jazz (2003-2007 and 2009-2012), City (2003-2009) and Civic (2003-2011).\n\n<p>â€œWe sincerely apologise for the inconvenience caused to customers once again. As customer safety is always Hondaâ€™s top priority, the company believes this replacement is necessary as a precautionary action and we urge affected customers to replace the defective Takata front airbag inflators as soon as possible.\n\n<p>â€œHonda Malaysia also appeals to affected Honda customers who have yet to replace their affected Takata front airbag inflators replaced to do so urgently as it may deploy with excessive internal pressure when activated, resulting in injury or fatality,â€ it said in a statement today.\nThe replacement stock for the Takata front airbag inflator for these 23,476 units will be available in stages, Honda Malaysia said, adding that it is doing its best to ensure 100% stock availability in the shortest period of time.\n\n<p>The replacement is free of charge and the cost will be borne by the company.\n\n<p>â€œHonda Malaysia would like to emphasise that all of its current selling models are not affected and the company will continue to uphold transparency and stringent controls to ensure customer safety,â€ it said.', '2019-11-02 06:57:49', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(7, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/8908dd86bc9083875144bb1f6f62e839.jpg', 'Program Subsidi Petrol B40', 10, 'TooWheel Media', '2019-10-08', 'uploads/7b3bcf585758a42a1e23edd7f15ef15c.jpg', 'uploads/d7bff33853c98149d86e93a6dc55e4e3.png', 'uploads/20b455126f30046d1d5d256534c35e0a.jpg', 'n0hC5zkFtlc', 'Program Subsidi Petrol (PSP) yang bakal dilaksanakan Januari 2020 menyalurkan bantuan tunai yang dikreditkan terus kepada akaun penerima Bantuan Sara Hidup (BSH) empat bulan sekali.\n\n\n\n\n', '<p>Kadar subsidi petrol adalah RM30 bagi kereta dan motosikal RM12 setiap sebulan.\n\n<p>Menteri Perdagangan Dalam Negeri dan Hal Ehwal Pengguna (KPDNHEP), Datuk Seri Saifuddin Nasution Ismail berkata, PSP menggantikan subsidi petrol sedia ada yang dinikmati oleh semua orang tanpa mengira kerakyatan dan pendapatan.\n\"Manakala kategori motosikal yang layak adalah motosikal 150cc dan ke bawah dan motosikal melebihi 150cc yang berumur tujuh tahun ke atas,\" katanya.\n\n<p>Beliau berkata, program PSP merupakan bentuk bantuan kewangan untuk membantu rakyat membiayai sebahagian kos penggunaan petrol.\n\n<p>â€œPrinsip bantuan yang hendak disampaikan oleh kerajaan adalah melalui pengagihan semula subsidi yang saksama (equitable redistribution) dan dasar berpandukan data (data driven policy).\n\n<p>â€œIni berdasarkan data ', '2019-10-10 03:05:34', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(10, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/991e7939547a9fb2613a50dc81391c13.jpg', 'Indian Motorcycle taps into 100-year roots with Japan relaunch', 14, 'BLOOMBERG ', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/22b61f6b94f93f7cec89db253dbe3337.jpg', 'undefined', 'undefined', 'null', 'TOKYO â€¢ A century ago, Indian Motorcycle Ltd was the brand of choice for Japanâ€™s police. They were called â€œaka-baiâ€ â€” or red bikes â€” because of their colour. Now, the maker of big American two-wheelers is seeking to recapture some of that glory with a brand relaunch.\n\n', '<p>Recreational vehicle maker Polaris Inc, which makes and sells Indian Motorcycle bikes, is betting that it can gain market share from entrenched foreign rivals such as BMW Motorrad and Harley-Davidson Inc.\nRecreational vehicle maker Polaris Inc, which makes and sells Indian Motorcycle bikes, is betting that it can gain market share from entrenched foreign rivals such as BMW Motorrad and Harley-Davidson Inc.\n\n<p>Instead of relying on a single distributor, the Medina Motors Inc, Minnesota-based company now has its own operations in Japan, with plans to double its store count to 30.\n\n<p>Even though Japanâ€™s population is shrinking and economic growth is tepid, the archipelago is one of the top five markets for heavy bikes.\n\n<p>Polaris is seeking to boost Indian Motorcycleâ€™s single-digit market share to 10% by 2025. It has taken direct control over local marketing, which it had outsourced after buying the Indian Motorcycle brand and relaunching it globally in 2011.\n\n<p>â€œWe werenâ€™t doing the rational thing in Japan,â€ said Kintaro Izumida, GM of Polaris in Japan.\n\n<p>He works out of an office in Yokohama with about a half-dozen other employees. â€œNow weâ€™re going to do that.â€\n\n<p>Harley-Davidson provides a rich target as the longtime market leader among import brands, with a 44% share of the 20,385 bikes sold last year, according to the Japan Automobile Importers Association.\n\n<p>Japanâ€™s domestic bike makers â€” Honda Motor Co Ltd, Kawasaki Motors Corp, Suzuki Motor Corp and Yamaha Motor Co Ltd â€” specialise in smaller- engine mass market bikes, with relatively few high-end motorcycles with engine displacements of more than 1000cc.\n\n<p>â€œThey are very strong manufacturers with really strong brand, but we donâ€™t really go head-to-head,â€ Steve Menneto, president of Polarisâ€™s Indian motorcycle division, said in a phone interview.\n\n<p>â€œFor a small island, itâ€™s amazing how much appreciation there is for motorcycles, and premium motorcycles at that.â€\n\n<p>The move comes as US motorcycle sales face headwinds, which is prompting American brands to look abroad for growth.\n\n<p>Last month, Harley-Davidson said it anticipates international sales to expand to half its business.\n\n<p>Japan is a natural market because it has the type of well-heeled buyer who can splurge for bikes that start at US$8,999 (RM37,706) for the Indian Scout, and top US$29,000 for the brandâ€™s Touring model.\n\n<p>Partly due to its international exposure, Polarisâ€™ sales rose in the first six months and the company forecasts a full-year gain in the low- to mid-teens over the segmentâ€™s 2018 revenue of US$546 million.\n\nIndian Motorcycleâ€™s retro-styling and long history in the US and overseas are the selling points in Japan, where brand identity is a key differentiator.\n\n<p>That extends beyond the bikes into lifestyle categories such as Indian-branded accessories and apparel, which account about a fifth of his divisionâ€™s revenue.\n\n<p>â€œThe awareness of the Indian brand in Japan is pretty strong,â€ said Izumida, noting it was the favoured brand of a famous sumo wrestler who became the father of pro wrestling in Japan. â€” Bloomberg', '2019-10-10 02:52:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(11, 'four_wheel', 'uploads/ebfa0d79f6c001689003efa3a6780395.jpg', 'Mercedes-Benz Malaysia launches B 200 Progressive Line: RM240k', 15, 'Car Sifu', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/8ef699d8f31147b7fdb13657d36f7be2.jpg', 'uploads/4a4dbc30a0daaac2b845930851cac365.jpg', 'uploads/e11f767c90a067a6ed057f4653e0db25.jpg', 'null', 'KUALA LUMPUR: Mercedes-Benz Malaysia has launched the new B 200 Progressive Line priced at RM239,888 on the road without insurance.\n\nPowered by a 1.33-litre 4-cylinder turbocharged engine with 163hp and maximum torque of 250Nm, it can acceleration from 0-100kph in 8.2 seconds.', '<p>It gets a Progressive Line exterior, which sports a radiator grille with silver-painted twin louvre and chrome insert, front apron with chrome insert, side sill panels and 18-inch 5-twin spoke light-alloy wheels.\n\n<p>Its interior features a wrap-around cabin with Artico leather upholstery in black, and a centre console with touch-based control and input system that comes with a black panel look similar to the E-Class.\n\n\n<p>Mercedes-Benz B-Klasse, denimblau Mercedes-Benz B-Class, denim blue\n\n\n<p>The ambient lighting with 64 colours and 10 colour worlds is unique in this segment, allows individual adjustments to suit the mood.\n\n<p>The new B-Class is also the second car model after the A-Class to feature the Mercedes-Benz User Experience (MBUX) multimedia system.\n\n<p>This comes with touch screen control as well as a high-resolution Widescreen cockpit, navigation display with Augmented Reality technology plus intelligent plus voice control with natural speech recognition, which is activated by saying â€œHey Mercedesâ€.\n\nDriving assistance systems include Blind Spot Assist â€“ radar sensors that monitor the areas directly alongside and behind the car, and helps warn the driver when there are objects detected while changing lanes.\n\n<p>It also has Active Brake Assist, which can help mitigate the severity of rear-end collisions with slower-moving, stopping or stationary vehicles ahead.\n\n \n\n<p>Mercedes-Benz B-Klasse, denimblau Mercedes-Benz B-Class, denim blue\nMercedes-Benz B 200 Progressive LineRM239,888 on the road without insuranceTransmission & Technology\n\nï‚·1.33-litre Inline-4 Turbocharged Petrol\nï‚·163hp at 5,500rpm\nï‚·350Nm at 1,620 â€“ 4,000rpm\nï‚·7G-DCT\nï‚·Comfort suspension\nï‚·DYNAMIC SELECT\n\n<p>Exterior Features\n\nï‚·18-inch 5-twin-spoke light-alloy wheels\nï‚·Electrically folding and adjustable exterior mirrors\nï‚·LED headlamps\nï‚·Progressive Line exterior\n\n<p>Comfort & Interior Features\n\nï‚·Ambient Lighting\nï‚·ARTICO leather black\nï‚·Automatically dimming mirrors\nï‚·Black open-pore linden wood trim\nï‚·Comfort seats\nï‚·Cruise control\nï‚·Double cup holder\nï‚·Electric adjustable front seats with memory function\nï‚·Leather multifunction sports steering wheel\nï‚·Progressive Line interior\nï‚·THERMATIC automatic climate control\n\n<p>Safety & Assistance Package\n\nï‚·Active Brake Assist\nï‚·Active Parking Assist with PARKTRONIC\nï‚·Anti-theft Alarm System\nï‚·Blind Spot Assist\nï‚·HANDS-FREE ACCESS\nï‚·KEYLESS-GO\nï‚·Kneebag\nï‚·PRE-SAFEÂ® System\nï‚·Reversing Camera\nï‚·TIREFIT\nï‚·Tyre Pressure Monitoring System\n\n<p>Multimedia System\n\nï‚·All-digital instrument display\nï‚·Android Auto\nï‚·Apple CarPlay\nï‚·MBUX multimedia system\nï‚·Media display\nï‚·Mercedes-Benz emergency call system\nï‚·Smartphone integration package\nï‚·Touchpad', '2019-10-10 03:02:49', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(12, 'four_wheel', 'uploads/88f43a213276d51bb73ed29d6410c142.jpg', 'All new Toyota Corolla launched starting at RM128,888', 15, 'RIZAL JOHAN ', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/5c5a778ad0cb7aaeaecd069d9580315c.jpg', 'uploads/cfa559454ce79772cd8113650f6c80c8.jpg', 'uploads/157b1f7037273f18dd3eb953ca21c751.jpg', 'null', 'PETALING JAYA: UMW Toyota Motor Sdn Bhd (UMWT), the official distributor of Toyota vehicles in Malaysia, has officially launched its all-new Toyota Corolla available in two variants.\n\n<p>Priced on-the-road without insurance, the 1.8E costs RM128,888 while the range-topping 1.8G gets tagged at RM136,888.', '\n\n<p>The new design of the Corolla follows the same dynamic theme of recently launched Toyota models. The headlights with LED (daytime running lights) DRL placed along the double J-shaped chrome-plated ornamentation emphasize the wide and dynamically-flowing headlamp design in the Corolla 1.8G.\n\n<p>Toyota Corolla (Mk12) - 38\nInside, the cabin has been designed to offer a spacious, modern and cohesive environment with levels of visual and tactile quality that reflect a prestigious sedan. Key to the feeling of spaciousness is a new instrument panel design with a more elegant appearance than before.\n\n\n<p>Both variants of the new Corolla use the 1.8-litre 2ZR-FE 4-cylinder DOHC 16-valve petrol engine with Dual VVT-i. The engine produces 139PS at 6,400rpm and peak torque of 172Nm at 4,000rpm.\n\n<p>It is mated with the 7-speed Sequential Shiftmatic (CVT) which is now enhanced with a new cooperative control and electronically-controlled throttle that provides a higher level of drivability, smoothness, quietness and fuel economy.\n\n<p>Toyota Corolla (Mk12) - 46\nIn terms of safety, both variants come with 7 SRS airbags and all seats are equipped with 3-point ELR seatbelts to help restrain occupants in the event of a collision. Other safety systems provided as standard features include Vehicle Stability Control (VSC) with Traction Control, Anti-lock Braking System (ABS), Hill-start Assist Control (HAC) and Tire Pressure Warning System.\n\n<p>The Corolla 1.8G, however, comes with Toyota Safety Sense (TSS)  which is the most advanced version and consists of 5 main systems â€“ Pre-Collision System (PCS), Lane Departure Alert (LDA) Steering Assist and Lane Tracing Assist (LTA), Dynamic Radar Cruise Control (DRCC) All Speed and Automatic High Beam (AHB).\n\n<p>Additionally, the car is also equipped with an Electric Parking Brake and Brake Hold feature for 1.8G.\n\n<p>Toyota Corolla (Mk12) - 45\nOther features in the new Corolla include an Optitron meter with 7â€ MID that can be switched between analogue and digital meter, panoramic view monitor with 3D image, electrochromic rearview mirror, SPORT mode with paddle shifter, rear sunshade and a wireless charger pad.\n\n<p>â€œThe all-new Toyota Corolla is one of the first models in Toyotaâ€™s range to adopt TNGA â€“ Toyota New Global Architecture. TNGA offers enormous flexibility to the designers and engineers to optimize designs for different types of vehicles,â€ said UMWTâ€™s President, Ravindran K.\n\n<p>Toyota Corolla (Mk12) - 32\nThere are 5 colour choices - Celestite Gray Metallic is a new iridescent shade while White Pearl CS, Silver Metallic, Red Mica Metallic and Attitude Black.\n\n<p>The new Corolla is imported in Completely Built-Up (CBU) form from Toyotaâ€™s regional production hub in Thailand.', '2019-10-10 03:13:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(13, 'four_wheel', 'uploads/145b2bcc4c9698b13aa3844a104a93cb.jpg', 'Mercedes-Benz Malaysia launches GLA 200 Style: RM224k', 15, 'CarSifu', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/33e2aeb253d9bdbb9725b206bcd3eb32.jpg', 'uploads/c3194a15bd8c7ad386f8e21a6c03ed47.jpg', 'uploads/730d4da2e7888d927607337f0f8a63e5.jpg', 'null', 'KUALA LUMPUR: Mercedes-Benz Malaysia has launched the new GLA 200 Style priced at RM223,888 on the road without insurance.\n\nPowered by a 1.6-litre 4-cylinder turbocharged engine with 156hp and torque of 250Nm, mated to a 7G-DCT transmission, it can acceleration from 0 -100kph in 8.1 seconds.', '<p>The Style Line exterior of the updated GLA 200 include 18-inch 5-twin-spoke light-alloy wheels and inserts in high-gloss chrome on the radiator trim in matt iridium silver.\n\n<p>The beltline trim strip and the load sill guard also feature an elegant chrome finish.\n\n<p>On the inside, the luxury seats finished in Artico man-made leather and MacapÃ¡ fabric feature a pattern inspired by tyre tracks.\n\n<p>Archivnummer: SSPIP85199\n\n\n<p>The GLA 200 Style also comes with Apple CarPlay and Android Auto, as well as a 8.0-inch media display.\n\n<p>Personalised vehicle settings can be chosen with the DYNAMIC SELECT switch in the upper control panel. These include characteristics of the engine, transmission, suspension and steering characteristics.\n\n<p>Safety features include Attention Assist - protection against drowsiness by preventing the risk of micro sleep increases especially on long journeys and when driving at night, as well as Active Brake Pre-Safe system, Active Parking Assist with Parktronic and LED High Performance headlamps.\n\n<p>Agility financing starts from RM3,288 and comes with a variety of packages.\n\n<p>Mercedes-Benz GLA 200 StyleRM223,888 on the road without insuranceTransmission & Technology\n\nï‚·1.6-litre 4 Cylinder Turbocharged Petrol\nï‚·156hp at 5,300rpm\nï‚·250Nm at 1,250 â€“ 4,000rpm\nï‚·7G-DCT\nï‚·Comfort suspension\nï‚·DYNAMIC SELECT\n\n<p>Exterior Features\n\nï‚·18-inch 5-twin-spoke light-alloy wheels\nï‚·Electrically folding and adjustable exterior mirrors\nï‚·LED headlamps\nï‚·Style Line exterior\n\n<p>Comfort & Interior Features\nï‚·4-way lumbar support\nï‚·Air conditioning system\nï‚·ARTICO leather/Macapa fabric\nï‚·Automatically dimming mirrors\nï‚·Black matrix-look trim\nï‚·Cruise control with limiter\nï‚·Cup holder\nï‚·Driver\'s seat, electrically adjustable with memory function\nï‚·Leather multifunction steering wheel\nï‚·Seat Comfort package\nï‚·Style Line interior\n\n<p>Safety & Assistance Package\n\nï‚·Active Brake Assist\nï‚·Active Parking Assist with PARKTRONIC\nï‚·Adaptive brake lights\nï‚·Anti-theft alarm system\nï‚·ATTENTON ASSIST\nï‚·KEYLESS GO starting function\nï‚·Kneebag\nï‚·PRE-SAFEÂ® system\nï‚·Reversing camera\nï‚·TIREFIT\nï‚·Tyre pressure monitoring system\n\n<p>Multimedia System\n\nï‚·8-inch Media Display\nï‚·Android Auto\nï‚·Apple CarPlay\nï‚·Audio 20 USB\nï‚·Preinstallation for Mercedes-Benz Link\nï‚·Smartphone integration package', '2019-10-10 03:21:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(14, 'four_wheel', 'uploads/87473604fe18b0539b9bfe650d62acbd.jpg', 'Alfa Romeo and Fiat in Malaysia: Passion remains strong', 15, 'THOMAS HUONG ', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/83694dcedd60828d321fc58ebe510380.jpg', 'uploads/9ed45c5d8e268e7c163d5d9939a359b4.jpg', 'uploads/f4ede5a6eca5260619c29a9ef56762e2.jpg', 'null', 'With choices aplenty for passenger car buyers in Malaysia, it can be tough for automotive marques to sustain or grow sales, with some even fading away to eventually exit the market.', '<p>This applies particularly to marques with fully imported cars, as the country\'s National Automotive Policy (NAP) supports local vehicle production via various incentives.\n\n<p>The NAP was launched in 2006 and had resulted in more restrictions and higher taxes for fully imported cars.\n\n<p>For example, Italian marque Alfa Romeo has not had an official presence here after Sime Darby Auto Italia (SDAI) gave up distribution rights in late 2013.\n\n\n<p>Low sales were blamed for the marque\'s exit (Alfa Romeo recorded only 38 imported units in Malaysia in 2012) and despite market talk that automotive conglomerate DRB-Hicom Bhd was interested in taking up Alfa Romeo distribution business, nothing has materialised to date.\n\n<p>This was a pity as veteran Alfa Romeo enthusiasts or Alfistis would recall that the police force in Malaysia were driving Italian models like the Berlina in the 70s, thanks to City Motors Group which was then the sole Alfa Romeo distributor in Malaysia.\n\n1968 Alfa Romeo 1750 Berlina \n1968 Alfa Romeo 1750 Berlina\n\n\n<p>Back then, City Motors Group also put Malaysia on the radar of Turin-headquartered Fiat SpA (the owner of Alfa Romeo) by selling a world record fleet volume of Alfa Romeo cars in a single deal.\n\n<p>Alfa Romeo cars developed a reputation among sporty car lovers for their handling and throaty exhaust roar.\n\n<p>The slogan Cuore Sportivo (Sporting Heart) personifies the passion that Alfistis have for their cars.\n\n<p>City Motors Group distributed Alfa Romeo cars including the iconic 2000 GTV sports car for nearly two decades before discontinuing the business in the late 1980s.\n\n1974 Alfa Romeo GTV 2000\n1974 Alfa Romeo GTV 2000\n\n\n<p>Later on, Milan Auto Sdn Bhd took over the franchise rights and the marque continued to thrive in Malaysia with models such as the 155 mid-sized family sedan introduced in the early 1990s.\n\n<p>In 2005, Sime Darby Motors acquired the franchise for Alfa Romeo and invested significantly in new 3S (sales, service and spare parts) outlets for the brand.\n\n<p>However, a few months later, growing the Alfa Romeo business became more difficult with the launch of the NAP in March 2006 to promote local vehicle manufacturing and assembly, and export-oriented Malaysian manufacturers.\n\n<p>Sime Darby Motors (SDM) was not keen to invest tens or hundreds of millions into production of completely knocked-down (CKD) Alfa Romeo cars, given that its sales target for 2006 was a mere 800 units (60% of expected sales from the 147 and 156, and 25% from GT models).\n\n<p>And despite SDM bringing in attractive models like the 159 sports sedan, GT and Brera coupes, the Spider cabriolet, the Mito hatchback and the Giulietta hot hatch - sales kept declining over the eight-year period until the company gave up the business in late 2013.\n\n2010 Alfa Romeo 159 JTS\n2010 Alfa Romeo 159 JTS\n\n\n<p>Meanwhile, sibling Italian marque Fiat also suffered a similar fate in Malaysia with local importer and distributor Torino Motor Industries (M) Sdn Bhd giving up the business at end-2009.\n\n<p>It was reported that the company had sold less than 60 Fiat cars in the four years after the NAP was launched, and blamed the low sales to high prices (RM100,000 and above) and small 1.4-litre engine capacities of some models.\n\n<p>Torino Motor Industries had distributed Fiat cars since 1992 and brought in models such as the sexy Coupe sports car, Grande Punto and Bravo GT hatchbacks, six-seater Multipla and seven-seater Ulysse MPVs (multi-purpose vehicles) and 500 A-segment city car.\n\n<p>In its heyday, the company used to enjoy brisk sales and could bask in annual registrations of 1,000 units of the old Fiat Punto.\n\n2008 Fiat Multipla\n2008 Fiat Multipla\n\n\n<p>Automotive industry observer Andrew Suresh noted that in the 70s, Continental marques like Alfa, Fiat, Opel and Saab had a strong presence in Malaysia before the influx of more affordable Japanese cars.\n\n<p>\"Sales of Continental marques declined and the Japanese cars took over the market as they were cheaper and developed a reputation for good fuel economy,\" said Andrew, who is the organiser of Asia Klasika Motor Festival - a motor show that promotes automotive heritage.\n\n<p>However, he recalled that Alfa Romeo and Fiat cars remained popular thanks to buyers who were passionate about their Italian styling, performance and responsive handling.\n\n<p>\"From the 60s till the 80s, Fiat was popular in Malaysia with cars like the 500, 600, 124 and 131. Fiat was known for its reliability and many people are driving them even today. The Fiat Coupe came in the 90s and stirred a lot of interest as it was almost like a mini Ferrari.\"\n\nFiat Coupe\nFiat Coupe\n\n\n<p>Andrew agreed that later on, hefty price tags and costly spare parts began to spell doom for the Italian marques here.\n\n<p>\"Only hard-core enthusiasts with deep pockets were willing to buy new cars.\"\n\n<p>However, he is confident the Italian marques will make a comeback in Malaysia someday.\n\n<p>\"They continue to be popular among car enthusiasts and Alfa Romeo cars are particularly popular among vintage and classic car lovers. The Giulia 1600 and 1300 which used to be valued at RM40,000 to RM50,000 nowadays can command RM90,000 to RM120,000.\"\n\n<p>He also noted the Alfa Romeo brand is still strong globally, and the brand has returned to F1 racing.\n\n\"Newer models like the 2.9-litre bi-turbo V6 engined Alfa Romeo Giulia Quadrifoglio have found buyers in Malaysia via grey importers despite the hefty price tags.\"', '2019-10-10 03:29:51', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(15, 'four_wheel', 'uploads/2559a9f77251d0a183913c1d7c7c805c.jpg', '2019 Tokyo Motor Show: Toyota luxury Granace MPV to be unveiled', 15, 'CARSIFU ', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/0fd6a03582fc59ce5e7aee198a3a4206.jpg', 'uploads/797c722aa9dc7cab706c61b65a7e4c7f.jpg', 'uploads/30be8283631011a130f755a77f8fc069.jpg', 'null', 'TOKYO: Toyota will unveil a new Granace van at the 46th Tokyo Motor Show 2019, and it\'s available in two seating layouts: the three-row six-seater, and the four-row eight-seater.', '<p>Powered by a 2.8-litre diesel engine mated to a six-speed automatic transmission, the front-wheel drive Granace uses a trailing-link rigid-axle rear suspension.\n\n<p>Designed for luxurious comfort, the second and third rows feature leather captain seats while wood grain decorations flow from the back of the front seats toward the side trim, and the LED side color illumination is gently lit.\n\n<p>The meter hood is wrapped in leather and genuine stitching further lends an air of quality.\n\n\n<p>Illumination for the road is courtesy of projective twin-lens LED headlamps and LED daytime running lamps.\n\n<p>It comes standard with the latest version of Toyota Safety Sense, featuring improved sensing functions that make use of the pre-collision safety system that detects pedestrians during the day and at night, as well as cyclists during the day.\n\n<p>Safety features include Intelligent Clearance Sonar with Parking Support Brakes (Stationary Objects) that helps reduce and/or mitigate damage from collisions during low-speed driving in parking lots.', '2019-10-10 03:46:02', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(16, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/8cd0a3b9845c429a6fc5f8eec050d375.jpg', 'Get your scoot on with BMW C 400 GT', 15, 'A. NACHI', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/b92358edb04d72b996c8ab7a761cf937.jpg', 'uploads/3f53ba41c100effce4d23e8042ac1440.jpg', 'uploads/f1a556a971066e150d4aa59deeaa3ca1.jpg', 'null', 'The first time I heard that BMW wanting to produce scooters, I found this direction to be rather awkward.\n\nBMW Motorrad had always been known for a brand that specializes in touring/adventure and sports bike and never anything besides those.\n\nBMW C 400 GT is a follow-up to the C 400 X launched last year. The C 400 GT is a 350cc machine offering 33.5hp and 35Nm of torque', 'Under the BMW Motorrad umbrella, scooters are positioned as urban mobility vehicles C 400 GT is designed to look sporty and be functional.\n\nEvery detail on the bike has been carefully thought through to make it appeal to the target audience.\n\nAt one glance, I found the bike bulky but from the front of the scooter, I realised that the scooter is slim.\n\nThis scooter comes with a wide and tall windshield which is very useful when I do outstation rides.\nHowever, I am not too thrilled as the windshield is not adjustable. The luggage compartment under the seat however, is generous.\n\nThis bike comes with a flexcase space which can be expanded downwards to carry more items.\n\nMeanwhile, the front floorboard is wide enough to place a shopping bag or a backpack. Under the seat are a 12V power outlet and an USB port to charge your mobile phone.\n\nThe 6.5-inch TFT screen is eye candy. The high resolution, colourful screen has all the basic information a rider needs like speed, engine rpm and fuel gauge.\n\nb6\n\n\nBesides those, the system can connect to your mobile phone using Bluetooth. The BMW Motorrad communication system allows easy access to your smartphone\'s contact list via the multi-controller, and thus to making phone calls on the go easy.\n\nIf you decide to enjoy your ride with your favourite playlist or the best route through the city via the GPS, the innovative turn-by-turn arrow display allows you to navigate quickly and safely.\n\nI found this machine a practical bike for daily commute. The slim motorcycle is ideal to whizz through traffic jams plus the torque is perfect for the countless stop-go ride in the city centre.\n\nb4\n\nKeeping the engine rev at 2,500rpm is the best for city riding. The power delivery is smooth and very predictable, making the bike easy to handle.\n\nAt 212kg, this bike is nimble and agile. The C 400 GT is a walk-in-the-park for any novice who is moving up from 250cc motorcycles.\n\nIt is obvious that the engine is designed to meet the needs of the city rides and long rides as well.\n\nb2\n\nIts Keyless Ride allows for a hassle-free ignition. On the highway, I was able to clock 120kph without running out of breath.\n\nFew of my riding buddies were quite impressed with the C 400 GT\'s punchy performance. Riding from Kuala Lumpur to Genting Highland to Bentong and back to Kuala Lumpur, I enjoyed the C 400 GT\'s excellent handling, stability and vibration-free performance on straight and winding roads.\n\nAnti-lock braking system (ABS) and automatic stability control (ASC) are standard safety features. Taking sharp and wide corners with this bike is effortless. I just had to manage the throttle at every entry and exit of the corners for a satisfying ride.\n\nb10\n\nAccelerating uphill is decent, keeping in mind that this is a scooter. The position of the handlebar, the specially designed seat and the relaxed foot peg position result in a perfect ergonomic triangle.\n\nThere is no doubt that this machine is built for a comfortable sitting position whether for short rides or long journeys.\n\nLike any other motorcycle, night riding is safe when the bike is equipped with really good lights. The C 400 GT\'s powerful light easily lights up dark roads ahead.\n\nb5\n\nThe front turn indicators are integrated into the trim panel while the rear ones are integrated into the tail light making the whole design sleek yet functional.\n\nI made a point to ride this bike on few bad roads in Kuala Lumpur which had a combination of potholes and uneven surface. The verdict is, the C 400 GT can handle rough stretches while keeping you comfortable on the saddle.\n\ntwo wheelers comes with a 35mm upside down front forks and twin rear shocks while its low centre of gravity makes the bike stable.\n\nb1\n\nBe it on the highland, city ride or long ride; the brakes on this machine costing RM45,590 (excluding GST) did what is designed to do.\n\nThe brakes on this scooter is from Bybrem. The twin front disks and a single rear are decent but the rear brake has a better bite. And not to forget the front and rear brakes get ABS.\n\nb9\nSPECIFICATIONS\n\nBMW C 400 GT\n\nEngine: 350cc, single cylinder, overhead cam, water cooled, 4-stroke, 4 valves\n\nMaximumpower: 33.5hp at 7,500rpm\n\nMaximumtorque: 35Nm at 6,000rpm\n\nFrontsuspension: 35mm telescopic forks\n\nRearsuspension: Twin rear suspension adjustment, preloaded\n\nFrontbrakes: 265mm double discs, 4 piston Bybre calipers\n\nRearbrakes: 265mm single disc, 1 piston Bybre caliper\n\nFuelCapacity: 12.8 litres Rrange: 360km (estimated)\n\nWetweight: 212kg\n\nPrice: RM45,590 (excluding GST)', '2019-10-11 13:55:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(17, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/07ff424d8903c0cc3d178657867bc693.jpg', '2020 Kawasaki Ninja 650 â€“ Finally, a TFT Screen!', 16, 'Wahid Ooi Abdullah', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/0d17917da3bf081f9d1daa259b0e7af1.jpg', 'uploads/ad8c77528ea9ba4b5a71b449f1f07809.jpg', 'uploads/f5b325c9d8c2083620256f4c1b526017.jpg', 'null', 'The 2020 Kawasaki Ninja 650 has been revealed.\nThereâ€™s finally a TFT screen.\nKawasaki also reworked the fairing and styling.', '<p>The 2020 Kawasaki Ninja 650 has been revealed. Kawasaki revised its looks and added some new features to make it an even better value for money.\n\n<p>The biggest news is of course the new 4.3-inch TFT screen. But it is not just a pretty screen as it includes features that could be found on bigger (read: more expensive) bikes. There is the auto contrast feature; Bluetooth connectivity for music and phone calls; GPS navigation via connection to a phone app; and thankfully a gear position indicator.\n\n\n\n<p>Also new are the LED headlamps. Kawasaki also revised the fairing to match that of the Ninja 400 and Ninja ZX-6R, for a more familial resemblance.\n\n\n\n<p>Since the Ninja 650 is considered a beginners bike and would be used for basically everything, the manufacturer revised the passengerâ€™s seat, too.\n\n\n\n<p>Last but not least, there are now sportier graphics, no doubt inspired by the World Superbike race team. The manufacturer and team are still flush from winning their fifth consecutive WorldSBK title.\n\n\n\n<p>The engine was left alone. The 648cc, DOHC, parallel-twin still produces 67 bhp and 66 Nm of torque. It still has plenty of low-RPM and midrange punch.\n\n\n\n<p>We shall see when it will arrive in Malaysia.', '2019-10-10 04:22:39', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(18, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/f7010aff556aba442328279cfc90d1db.jpg', 'New Colours for 2019 Yamaha Ego Avantiz', 16, ' Wahid Ooi Abdullah', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/3375f938845566c68dc9790dee29be8f.jpg', 'uploads/9028c1404b0d33223758de74d9e2bcb3.jpg', 'uploads/3a401ec9fa42f369fd1cdef13ac3c10a.jpg', 'null', 'There are four new colours for the 2019 Yamaha Ego Avantiz.\nThe model has been sold since 2016.\nIt continues to be popular among Malaysia motorcyclists.', '<p>Mention the name â€œYamahaâ€ in the small motorcycle segment and the Ysuku (Y15ZR) is the first model that comes to mind. Truth is, other models sell just as well. Thatâ€™s why Hong Leong Yamaha Motor (HLYM) has just rolled out new colours for the 2019 Yamaha Ego Altiz.\n\n<p>Launched in 2016, the Ego Avantiz is the most popular twist-and-go scooter in its segment despite the onslaught of competitors.\n\n\n <p>The Yamaha is powered by a 125cc, air-cooled, SOHC engine which utilises Yamahaâ€™s Blue Core set of solutions for optimum operational. The criteria include efficiency in cooling, low friction and lubrication. Consequently, the engine produces more power and torque while minimising fuel consumption and emissions.\n\n<p>Yamaha scooters always feature lots of storage space and the Ego Avantiz has a 14-litre underseat storage capacity.\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, this model pioneered the use of LED headlamps and taillamp in its segment.\n\nMore importantly, the bike has a low seat height, making it accessible to anyone. But most important of all is its very affordable price.\n\n\n\n\n<p>So, itâ€™s easy to see why the bike is still popular among Malaysian motorcyclists. As such, HLYM introduced four new colours for the 2019 Yamaha Ego Avantiz.\n\nThey are Blue, Cyan, Grey and Red. Pricing remains unchanged at RM 5,536 (basic sales price and not on-the-road). They will be available from this month onwards.', '2019-10-10 04:30:34', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(19, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/33c93369e5aa863801fdb0bdf6132816.jpg', 'New 2020 KTM 1290 Super Duke R Incoming?', 16, ' Wahid Ooi Abdullah', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/ab283a2ed4db411fe351799e101cc6c7.jpg', 'uploads/9801e703ec15dfe8b2ca90437b41680d.jpg', 'undefined', 'hI1hBwMv5cU', 'KTM released a teaser video for a new Duke.\nWe are inclined to believe it is the 2020 KTM 1290 Super Duke R.\nWill we see a power increase in the face of upcoming new supernakeds?', 'Before we continue, weâ€™d like to say, â€œHereâ€™s another teaser video.â€ This time itâ€™s from KTM with the hashtag #GetDuked. But certain frames in the teaser got us to believe that itâ€™s going to be the new 2020 KTM 1290 Super Duke R.\n\nEagle-eyed viewers freezes certain frames in the video and pointed out that there were glimpses of a bike with a single-sided swingarm. Thatâ€™s the dead giveaway for a 1290 Super Duke R, since a revised 1290 Super Duke GT had been introduced for this year.\n\nThe prototype 2020 KTM 1290 Super Duke R was spotted on a number of occasions. If the pictures are anything to go by, the new bike will have a new frame and subframe. The new bikeâ€™s frame looks more sparse, rather than taking on the appearance of a ladder. As for the new subframe, it resembles the aluminium one used on the 790 Duke.\n\nWe were thinking of either the rumoured 490 Duke or 890 Duke initially. But thereâ€™s still no confirmation if KTM is indeed working on these two.\n\nThis new bike will be unveiled on 5th November 2019, the opening day of EICMA.\n\nBut the most important question is probably whether weâ€™ll see a power increase for the new 1290 Super Duke R. The model has held the title of the most powerful supernaked for many years. However, Ducati is set to introduce the Streetfighter V4 while Kawasaki has teased with a supercharged â€œZâ€ model which is a naked H2 in essence.\n\nLet the arms race begin.', '2019-10-10 04:36:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(20, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/1b1484fa82042302ae7fd60988e96a9e.jpg', 'Here it is! The 2020 Triumph Street Triple RS!', 16, 'Wahid Ooi Abdullah', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/eb5eb70fb7bbdc6020154973ade844fc.jpg', 'uploads/1ab86070002fbbe5ae3b0ebc7a61c068.jpg', 'uploads/b66a6918d51f4f6367ccf934393aabe6.jpg', 'null', 'The 2020 Triumph Street Triple RS breaks cover.\nIts engine receives a power boost.\nIt also receives updated looks and lost some weight.', 'The 2020 Triumph Street Triple RS breaks cover after Triumphâ€™s teases over the last couple of months.\n\nThe new bike retains the Street Tripleâ€™s classic silhouette, but itâ€™s apparent that Triumph pared it down to look even more purposeful than ever. The headlamps were updated to look fiercer. There are new radiator flanks, exposing more of the frame. Triumphâ€™s scalpel pared away excess weight, ending up with a bike which weighs only 166 kg dry. The manufacturer claims that itâ€™s the lightest bike in its category.\n\nOver to the engine. While the 2020 bike was revealed in preparation for Euro 5 emission, the engine gained power, courtesy of the lessons learned in Moto2 racing. (Triumph is the exclusive engine supplier to the championship.)\n\nThe three-cylinder architecture remains the same and includes two catalytic convertors. Despite that, it receives a 9-percent power boost. It now produces 121 bhp and 77.3 Nm of torque, compared to the previous 116 bhp and 76 Nm of torque. That doesnâ€™t appear to be a lot on paper, of course, but you can look forward to a punchier midrange combined with a more responsive throttle (the previous bikeâ€™s throttle was already super responsive and smooth!). The gains and smoother powerband are the courtesy of a new exhaust cam, besides the high precision machining of the crankshaft, clutch and balancer.\n\nThe previous RSâ€™s chassis and suspension are already in the ballpark, hence carried over to the new bike. The front forks remain the 41mm upside-down Showa BFF, while the rear mono shock is the Ohlins STX40.\n\nBraking duties are handled by a pair of Brembo M50 monobloc 4-piston callipers gripping a pair of 310mm discs up front and a Brembo single-piston calliper out back.\n\nAnd as we speculated, there is a new TFT screen armed with Bluetooth connectivity. Through the MyTriumph app, the rider can receive navigation prompts, manage music and calls and control his GoPro action camera. The five riding modes i.e. Track, Sport, Road, Rain and rider customisable are also enhanced.\n\nThe previous Triumph Street Triple RS remains the most fun bike weâ€™ve tested to this point, so we canâ€™t wait to test this new one!', '2019-10-11 13:53:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(21, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/7122ada27661f6bdf3d0279423c0ac39.jpg', 'MV Agusta Finds Funding for the Next Five Years', 16, 'Wahid Ooi Abdullah', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/feef13399366feea6a7b89ebe516e0fe.jpg', 'uploads/75451010109392668f8917350b14e829.jpg', 'uploads/c31c8eda3676339823d6f77fdcaf2421.png', 'null', 'MV Agusta brand announced securing funding for the next five years.\nThe news also brought shake-ups in the companyâ€™s management.\nThe manufacturer is looking forward to invest more in the global network in the next two years.', '<p>Great new for the storied MV Agusta brand as it announced the securing of funding for the next five years.\n\n<p>The funding allows the oft-tumultuous brand to continue developing bikes into the near future. A new business plan is according drawn up and sees the manufacturer targeting an annual sales goal of 25,000 motorcycles next year.\n\n<p>They will continue to concentrate on premium motorcycles, but will add mid-sized bikes. The firm tied up with Loncin Motor Company in China recently to produce four motorcycles between 350cc to 500cc.\n\n<p>The plan also calls for â€œstrongâ€ investment in MV Agustaâ€™s global distribution and service network over the next two years, focusing on the United States, Europe and Asia.\n\n<p>Following the news is also the announcement of a revision in the MV Agusta management line-up.\n\n<p>Giovanni Castiglioni will be moved to the role of an advisor after steadfastly holding on to the companyâ€™s helm for a number of decades. Timur Sardarov had taken over as Chairman of the Board and CEO in December 2018, since the funding comes from his family. He will be joined by Massimo Bordi and Paolo Bettin.\n\n<p>Massimo Bordiâ€™s name should be no stranger to many. He was the father of the four-valve, liquid-cooled V-Twin engine for Ducati. It was he who challenged the convention put forth by Fabio Taglioni such an arrangement couldnâ€™t be made.\n\n<p>Bordi will assume the role of Executive Vice Chairman. He had served as General Manager for MV Agusta and Cagiva during Claudio Castlglioniâ€™s (Giovanniâ€™s father) tenure.\n\n<p>On the other hand, Betting will be the new Chief Financial Officer.\n\n<p>Goh Brothers is now holding the role of official aftersales provider for MV Agusta in Malaysia. Will this plan also see them expanding to sales?', '2019-10-10 05:16:26', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(22, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/a510b57288a8c8a7c8b504be49c33b86.jpg', 'Thailand May Ban Lane Splitting for Big Bikes', 16, 'Wahid Ooi Abdullah', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/3bf812da4b74d6ef8a9836330ac6cd43.jpg', 'undefined', 'undefined', 'null', 'Malaysian bikers beware: Thailand may roll out a number of new rulings.\n\nLane splitting ban and an 80km/h speed limit for big bikes is being proposed.\n\nMotorcycle license is required when renting a scooter.', 'Thailand Transport Ministry may ban lane splitting for big bikes and limit their speed to 80km/h in urban areas.\n\nThe countryâ€™s Deputy Permanent Secretary for Transport Chirute Vialachitra said that the ban would require big bike riders to wait for traffic lights behind other vehicles. The 80km/h speed limit applies to urban and community areas i.e. villages and towns.\n\nAdditionally, big bike riders are to undergo specially-designed tests to obtain their driving licenses. The government plans to set up special test fields and simulators for big bike riders. The simulations will present danger-prone situations to train riders on safety aspects.\n\nBut more importantly, foreign tourists are required to show their motorcycle license when renting motorcycles in the country. The requirement is already in existence but not enforced. This is in view of the spate of foreigner deaths while riding motorcycles.\n\nA timeline for enacting the new rules has not been provided, said Mr. Chirute but will be finalized in 30 days before seeking cabinet approval. He hopes the new measures will be in place by year end.\n\nShould the new ruling be approved, Malaysian bikers should beware of them when riding into Thailand.', '2019-10-11 13:56:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(23, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/173be2a80ee76b2d2b087741cca12d4a.jpg', 'Sikh Riders from Santana Riderz Malaysia Club Rides 16,000km to Raise Fund for Children with Cancer', 16, ' Wahid Ooi Abdullah', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/db8a520956842bc1829ead2faa04492b.jpg', 'uploads/cc0a661eec3e6874933c1d2616db8793.jpg', 'uploads/ac2991c52e73293754afc804764141d2.jpg', 'null', 'A group of 17 Sikh riders from the Santana Riderz Malaysia Club will ride 16,000km to Pakistan.\nThe objective is to raise awareness and funds for children with cancer.\nThe ride is conjunction with the 550th anniversary of Guru Nanak Devji, founder of Sikhism.', 'Santana is a Malaysian oldest biking group and it was formed by group of young Sikh boys to have fun rides back in 1979. This club is a non-profit organisation and with God blessings always seek to provide support to those needy ones.\nA group of 17 Sikh riders from the Santana Riderz Malaysia Club will ride 16,000km to Pakistan in order to raise funds for children with cancer.\n\nThe ride will see them travelling through five countries, and will raise awareness and donations for child cancer patients of the National Cancer Society of Malaysia. The convoy is held in conjunction with the 550thanniversary of Guru Nanak Devji, founder of Sikhism.\n\nThe ride is slated to be flagged off from Gurdwara Sahib Polis at Jalan Balai Polis, Kuala Lumpur on 25th September 2019.\n\nThey will then ride through Thailand, Myanmar, and India and finally arriving in Nankana Sahib, Pakistan. Nankana Sahib is the birthplace Guru Nanak Devji.\n\nâ€œWe hope weâ€™ll be able to ease the hardship of families who are suffering both emotionally and financially. (That is) in line with the theme of our ride â€˜Sarbat Da Bhalaâ€™ which means blessings for everyone irrespective of race or religion,â€ said club president Jas Pall Singh.\n\nHe also added that the club chose NCSM because they aim to help the children regardless of race, religion and background.\n\nOn top of fundraising, the group also planned a â€œ550 Trees Planting Project.â€\n\nYou may contribute to the funds through this website <a href=\"https://www.peoplegiving.org/campaign/5-takhts-ride-to-india-for-cancer-charity-ride-2019\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.peoplegiving.org/campaign/5-takhts-ride-to-india-for-cancer-charity-ride-2019.</a>', '2019-10-11 13:50:01', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0),
(24, 'two_wheel', 'uploads/3a1debaa85fda976732be6398e39b93c.jpeg', 'Petrol Subsidy Proposed for Below 125cc Bike Owners, Removal of RON95 Subsidy', 16, 'Wahid Ooi Abdullah ', '2019-10-10', 'uploads/61ee7bbbea3b3b1ddb0d75f3ca7cfb2d.jpeg', 'undefined', 'undefined', 'null', 'Minister of Domestic Trade and Consumer Affairs announced that the proposal for petrol subsidy is ready.\nThe new subsidy plan hopes to help the B40 group.\nThe proposed subsidy will apply to owners of motorcycles below 125cc.', '<p>After more than a year deliberation, the Minister of Domestic Trade and Consumer Affairs announced that the proposal for petrol subsidy is ready.\n\n<p>If given the green light by the Cabinet, the government will employ a number of safeguards to ensure the that B40 group receives the subsidy. The measures proposed are in view of unreliable data which often plagues decision-making among government agencies in Malaysia.\n\n<p>The Malay Mail quoted sources who said that the government has a better database now. It is drawn up based on data from pension fund contributions, the applicantâ€™s payslips, and vehicle ownership data with the Road Transport Department (JPJ). The Star reported that the government will also look at household electric bills that amount to between RM 100 and RM 200 monthly. Also, the assistance only applies to those whose monthly household income is less RM 3,900.\n\n<p>As for the amount of subsidy, the Ministry may be adhering to Minister of Finance Lim Guan Engâ€™s proposal in November. The plan calls for subsidising owners of motorcycles below 125cc and cars below 1,500cc with a minimum of 30 sen per litre of RON95 petrol.\n\n<p>The total amount of subsidised petrol is 40 litres for motorcycles and 100 litres for cars per month. The subsidy amounts to RM 12 for motorcycles and RM 30 for cars per month. The amount will be transferred to the recipientsâ€™ bank accounts on a monthly basis.\n\n<p>The current price of subsidised RON95 is capped at RM 2.08 per litre. Prices would fluctuate according to a weekly float once the subsidy is removed and may see an increase to RM 2.49 per litre.\n\n<p>It was revealed that government currently spends an average of RM 133 million a week on fuel subsidies.', '2019-10-10 05:45:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0);
